spans.text: the bards of the song , gray-haired Ullin
the blast that rushed unfrequent from the hill
had they seen the grave of Salgar
thy clouds ; stars of the night appear
from the toil of the chase
my voice be heard over the heath
half-drowned in the storms of the hill
in the storms of the hill
my friends , by the stream of the sounding rock
the fall of Morar , first of mortal men
among the sons of the plain
thee no more ; thy bow shall lie in the hall , unstrung
the hunter's eye the grave of the mighty Morar
scarce a leaf , long grass which whistles in the wind
thee no more ; nor the dark wood be lightened with the splendour of thy steel
they shall hear of the fallen Morar
the death of his son , who fell in the days of his youth
Why bursts the sigh of Armin
with its music , to melt and please the soul
the dark heath ! streams of the mountains , roar !
fair as the moon on the hills of Fura
fair was the hope of their friends
disguised like a son of the sea : fair was his skiff on the wave ; white his locks of age
for her brother and her father
in the spoils of the chase
fierce Erath on the shore : he seized and bound him to an oak
he panted on the rock and expired
among the grass of the rocks
when the north lifts the waves on high
see the ghosts of my children
the first among a thousand bards
as they pass along , why does Ossian sing
